Class MapInfo

java.lang.Object
  main.MapInfo

public class MapInfo
extends java.lang.Object

MapInfo is a singleton design pattern class (no direct instantiation) used for holding map information. Code for this found here:

  • http://www.javacoffeebreak.com/articles/designpatterns/index.html
  • http://www.javabeginner.com/learn-java/java-singleton-design-pattern

    • Author:
    Nicolai, Lasse

    Method Detail

    getMapInfo

    public static MapInfo getMapInfo(CanvasMaze canvasMaze,
                                 CanvasMenu canvasMenu)
    When first called, the getMapInfomethod creates a singleton instance, assigns it to a member variable, and returns the singleton. Subsequent calls will return the same singleton, and all is well with the world. Method is declared syncronized to prevent two threads from calling the getMapInfo method at the same time.

    Returns:
    mapObject holds static instance of MapInfo object.

    clone

    public java.lang.Object clone()
                       throws java.lang.CloneNotSupportedException
    We override the inherited superclass implementation of clone() to prevent cloning of the singleton. For now the only superclass is Object, in which clone() is protected, but later on we might inherit from another class that implements clone()

    Overrides:
    clone in class java.lang.Object
    Returns:
    nothing, throws exception
